UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2408
1 AN ACT relating to teachers of exceptional children.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 157 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Notwithstanding any other statute to the contrary, a public school teacher, or a
6 teacher employed at the Kentucky School for the Blind or Kentucky School for
7 the Deaf operated by the Department of Education, who holds a professional
8 certificate for teaching exceptional children, and who is employed in a classroom
9 teacher position requiring the certificate, shall receive an annual salary
10 supplement of ten thousand dollars ($10,000) for each year the conditions are
11 met during the life of the certificate. If an annual supplement amount
12 appropriated by the General Assembly is less than ten thousand dollars ($10,000),
13 the local board may provide an additional supplement up to the amount required
14 for the total annual supplement to equal ten thousand dollars ($10,000). The
15 supplement shall be added to:
16 (a) The teacher's base salary on the local board's single salary schedule and
17 shall be considered in the calculation for contributions to the Kentucky
18 Teachers' Retirement System; or
19 (b) The state-employed teacher's base salary and shall be considered in the
20 calculation for contributions to the Kentucky Teachers' Retirement System.
21 (2) If a teacher who holds a professional certificate for teaching exceptional children
22 becomes no longer employed in a classroom teacher position requiring the
23 certificate, the supplement provided under subsection (1) of this section shall
24 cease.
25 (3) A local board of education or the Department of Education shall request
26 reimbursement for these purposes from the fund to support education excellence
27 described in KRS 157.330
